Abubakar Ahmed Sabo, Village Head of Loko, Nasarawa state has given insight as to why the deposed Emir of Kano, Muhammad Sanusi II was relocated from Loko to Awe after spending one night. The Village Head who spoke on the Hausa service of the BBC and monitored from Kaduna said, the former Emir is too big to stay in a village like his, which according to him lacks social amenities that will make his stay comfortable. According to the Village Head, “Emir (Sanusi) is too big for this village. What I mean is that, Emir Sanusi is a high ranking personality. He is supposed to be under air conditioner, but we don’t have electricity to give him that. “We received him very well, but with mix feelings. We were sad because of what happened to him, baceuse when your fellow human being is in this kind of situation, you are expected to be with him in that situation, but, we were happy that, our village came to limelight; that, of all the cities in Nigeria, it was Loko that was chosen for him to come to.” Asked whether he observed any bad feeling in Emir Sanusi, the Village Head said, He (Sanusi) was not disturbed at all, and that, he slept well very well. “He was not disturbed at all, in fact, he slept well very well. He accepted his destiny. He even said, he won’t challenge his dethronement in court. He also called the people to support the new Emir. In fact, he sent text message congratulating the new Emir and the new Emir, Alhaji Aminu Ado Bayero replied him.” He said. On their conversation, the Village Head of Loko disclosed that, Sanusi advised them (traditional rulers) to know the way to relate with politicians. “He advised that we should know the way to relate with politicians, because there is nothing that brought this dethronement except politics.” Asked whether the Emir had any regret in his actions which were suspected to have brought about his dethronement, Sarki Sabo said, Emir Sanusi does not have any regret, “because he said he did not commit any offence.” 